27/08/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The government has demanded that expert teams assembled by cabinet ministries complete work on the lengthy European Commission questionnaire that could prove crucial to eventual EU membership. 
In all, 29 issues must still be addressed, according to a statement Tuesday (26 August) by European Integration Minister Neven Mimica.
In other news Tuesday, two members of parliament from the nationalist Croatian Democratic Union (HDZ) -- Ante Beljo and Dario Vukic -- left the HDZ and joined the smaller right-wing Croatian True Revival (HIP) party. 
Miroslav Tudjman, son of the late Croatian President Franjo Tudjman, leads the HIP. 
(HINA, BBC - 26/08/03)
